			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				What a wonderful little spell. Not very useful in a kite situation or regular solo but for a group.... it's nifty. Cast the spell onto the /assist of your group leader and give the tanks a little break. The creature still fights but not nearly as hard. Still, I think it's most useful because it gives me something to cast in combat that works my div skill =)<BR>
<BR>
As for the last comment about dot's doing max... that isn't true. DoT's _only_ do max on a parked target. Root, or parked in melee. If that thing moves at all the effects are reduced. Stinks but heck, not like druids need any more help with soloing.<BR>
<BR>
Did my eyes read right? Someone out there uses and Pogonip? What a crap spell. Not at all efficent on mana and doesn't hit half the time even with the skill maxed. :shrug: something new everyday.<BR>
<BR>
Ustke Pathwalker<BR>
Brell
