			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok, this is basically how this spell works (and dont say it doesn't because i used the lower levle version of this spell with my shaman) What you do is this.  Simply snare, cast this spell, and then walk out of the way of them, and they will just keep going in that direction.  Unless u get in front of them or the spell wears off, you will have no problem.  Very effective.  It acts as if feared or running, so the DOTs do max damage.  (i think...not sure about the DOTs doing max damage or not)<BR>
<BR>
Hope this is helpful!<BR>
<BR>
Aluludar D'Arbre<BR>
24th Druid<BR>
Mith Marr<BR>

