	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I thought sunbeam was useless until I started hunting in The OverThere at level 34ish.  I found that While we were pulling animals there (use your lvl 19 terrorize animal spell w/fear), sometimes our casters and healer would get attacked by Cock's and Sarnaks (non-animals).  Naturally, the casters/healers run around trying to get away.  I've found that you can blind the attacking mob thats after the caster, and it will flee for about 12 seconds, allows the caster/healer to get out of the mobs agro range.  Of course, it'll agro you now, but you can now snare and manage the problem.  VERY useful spell, its also good when hunting tumps-- you can snare/dot...when dot wears off, blind it so u can get enuf time to get that dot off again, repeat.<BR>
<BR>
 -- Cozumel
				</font>
			</td>

